swapaxes is NumPy-dialect alias for torch.transpose (https://pytorch.org/docs/stable/generated/torch.swapaxes.html#torch.swapaxes). If the rest is in Torch-lingo, shouldn't it be:
```python
class SwapAxes(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, dim1: int, dim2: int) -> None:
        super().__init__()
        self.dim1 = dim1
        self.dim2 = dim2

    def forward(self, x: torch.Tensor) -> torch.Tensor:
        return x.transpose(self.dim1, self.dim2)
```

